"Our line must be very clear: We do not accept and do not want dirty votes and votes bought. We don't care. We want them away." He said the secretary of the Pd, Elly Schlein, from the stage of "Let's go!", commenting on yesterday's poll in Bari.
&nbsp;
<div </div "The story of yesterday, of Triggiano, and the investigations of the exchange vote, if the accusations are confirmed, are very serious - the secretary continued -. And first of all they hurt those who commit themselves every day to return dignity to politics in a country where 50% of the electricians and voters stopped voting. In front of these facts the solution is not the easiest, point your finger at someone else, someone outside of themselves, but look inside. And the democratic party intends to do it all the way. He intends to do it with self-critical and determination. Because we are not immune to attempts at infiltration, but we must together become it: never allow such things to happen." And concludes: "It is not denying the participation that contrasts infiltration. It is not denying more democracy that the space of those who want to condition it is contrasted. That's the opposite."
